    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1867-06-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1867-06-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="345"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d345">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. de
                        Stoeckl</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1867-06-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 2, 1867</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. de Stoeckl:</hi> I have received a despatch
                    from Mr. Clay, in which he gives us the pleasing information that his Imperial
                    Highness, the <pb facs="0470" n="402" xml:id="pg_402"/> Grand Duke Alexis,
                    contemplates visiting our country during the present year. Whenever it may be
                    convenient I would be happy to confer with you upon this subject at this
                    department.</p>
                <p>Faithfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWAKD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Edward de Stoeckl</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,
                            &amp;c., &amp;c</hi>.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
